Proposed timetable:
# TravelPlan: Frankfurt to Dublin by Car and Ferry — September 5–10, 2026

| Day 1 — 2026-09-05 — Drive to Cherbourg | Day 2 — 2026-09-06 — Ferry to Dublin | Day 3 — 2026-09-07 — Dublin city and pubs | Day 4 — 2026-09-08 — Howth coastal hike | Day 5 — 2026-09-09 — Bray Head and return ferry | Day 6 — 2026-09-10 — Arrive Cherbourg and drive home |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Drive Frankfurt to Cherbourg** [transport] 07:00–18:30 @ Frankfurt am Main, Germany to Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€215.00) — Drive from Frankfurt to Cherbourg via Saarbrücken, Metz, Reims, Paris/Caen and N13 to the ferry port. Source estimates: 880–910 km, about 8h45–9h30 driving before breaks; allow extra time for rests and Paris/Reims congestion. Estimated one-way fuel/tolls: €180–€215. — Links: [link 1](https://tollguru.com/toll-calculator-europe), [link 2](https://www.autoroutes.sanef.com/en/my-journey/price-of-my-journey) | **1. Breakfast and ferry-prep in Cherbourg** [meal] 09:00–10:00 @ Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€15.00) — Easy morning after the long drive; fuel the car and prepare passport, vehicle registration, insurance and ferry booking documents. | **1. Arrive Dublin Port and drive to city centre** [transport] 11:45–12:45 @ Dublin Port Terminal 1 to Dublin city centre (€4.00) — Disembark and drive from Dublin Port Terminal 1 toward the city centre. Source-backed estimate: about 10–15 minutes once clear of port controls; allow up to an hour for disembarkation and traffic. — Links: [link 1](https://www.dublinport.ie/to-from/), [link 2](https://www.tii.ie/en/news/press-releases/toll-charge-increase-from-1st-january-2026/) | **1. Breakfast at Two Pups** [meal] 08:00–09:00 @ 74 Francis St, The Liberties, Dublin 8, Ireland (€15.00) — Budget breakfast café option before the coastal hike day. — Links: [link 1](http://www.twopupscoffee.com/) | **1. Check out of Abigails Hostel** [lodging] 08:00–08:30 @ Abigails Hostel, Dublin city centre, Ireland (€0.00) — Check out and leave luggage in the car or with hostel storage if available. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lp72ced?checkin=2026-09-06&checkout=2026-09-09&rooms=1&adults=1&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoxLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR) | **1. Arrive Cherbourg and disembark** [transport] 12:00–13:00 @ Gare Maritime, Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€0.00) — Arrive at Cherbourg and clear port/disembarkation before the long drive back to Frankfurt. — Links: [link 1](https://www.ferryhopper.com/en/ferry-routes/direct/dublin-cherbourg) |
| **2. Check in: L'Autre Lieu, Cherbourg** [lodging] 18:30–19:00 @ L'Autre Lieu, Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€61.00) — Budget accommodation with free Wi‑Fi and secured parking listed in the hotel result. Selected as a practical overnight before the ferry. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lp656d6d8f?checkin=2026-09-05&checkout=2026-09-06&rooms=1&adults=1&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoxLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR) | **2. Lunch at Théo Grill** [meal] 12:00–13:15 @ 12 Rue Victor Grignard, 50100 Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€25.00) — Casual pre-ferry lunch in Cherbourg; moderate budget and highly rated. — Links: [link 1](https://theogrill.eatbu.com/) | **2. Lunch at Darkey Kelly's** [meal] 13:00–14:15 @ 19 Fishamble St, Christchurch Pl, Temple Bar, Dublin 8, Ireland (€25.00) — Traditional Irish pub lunch, moderate price, strong rating and central location. — Links: [link 1](http://darkeykellys.ie/) | **2. DART Dublin to Howth** [transport] 09:15–10:00 @ Dublin city centre to Howth DART Station (€3.00) — Take the DART from central Dublin to Howth. Source-backed estimate: around 26–31 minutes from central Dublin stations; use a Leap Card for the lower fare. — Links: [link 1](https://www.irishrail.ie/), [link 2](https://www.irishrail.ie/en-ie/station/howth) | **2. Breakfast at Two Pups** [meal] 08:45–09:30 @ 74 Francis St, The Liberties, Dublin 8, Ireland (€15.00) — Budget breakfast before the Bray Head hike and ferry departure day. — Links: [link 1](http://www.twopupscoffee.com/) | **2. Lunch in Cherbourg before drive** [meal] 13:00–14:00 @ Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€20.00) — Simple meal before the return drive. |
| **3. Dinner at Le Plouc 2** [meal] 19:30–21:00 @ 59 Rue au Blé, 50100 Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€30.00) — Traditional French dinner in Cherbourg; moderate price level and highly rated in restaurant search. — Links: [link 1](https://www.restaurantleplouc2.fr/) | **3. Check in for Cherbourg–Dublin ferry** [transport] 14:30–16:30 @ Gare Maritime, Quai de Normandie, 50100 Cherbourg-en-Cotentin, France (€0.00) — Arrive at Gare Maritime, Cherbourg for vehicle check-in. Irish Ferries guidance found: car passengers must be checked in at least 60 minutes before departure; arriving earlier gives buffer. — Links: [link 1](https://www.ferryhopper.com/en/ferry-routes/direct/dublin-cherbourg), [link 2](https://www.directferries.com/dublin_cherbourg_ferry.htm) | **3. Check in: Abigails Hostel** [lodging] 14:30–15:00 @ Abigails Hostel, Dublin city centre, Ireland (€64.00) — Central Dublin hostel option from hotel search at about €32/night; budget-friendly for a solo traveler. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lp72ced?checkin=2026-09-06&checkout=2026-09-09&rooms=1&adults=1&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoxLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR) | **3. Howth Cliff Path coastal hike** [attraction] 10:00–14:00 @ Howth Cliff Path Loop, Howth, Co. Dublin, Ireland (€0.00) — Coastal hike from Howth DART/harbour using the signed cliff routes. Official-style access info found: open year-round, daylight strongly recommended, free access; expect uneven, exposed paths and cliff-edge sections. — Links: [link 1](https://www.sportireland.ie/outdoors/walking/trails/howth-cliff-path-loop), [link 2](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Out+Out+Club) | **3. DART Dublin to Bray** [transport] 09:45–10:30 @ Dublin city centre to Bray Daly Station, Co. Wicklow (€3.00) — Take the southbound DART to Bray. Source-backed estimate: about 36 minutes; use Leap Card if available. — Links: [link 1](https://www.irishrail.ie/) | **3. Drive Cherbourg to Reims / motorway rest break** [transport] 14:00–19:00 @ Cherbourg-en-Cotentin to Reims area, France (€110.00) — First half of return drive from Cherbourg toward eastern France via Caen/Paris bypass/Reims direction. — Links: [link 1](https://tollguru.com/toll-calculator-europe), [link 2](https://www.autoroutes.sanef.com/en/my-journey/price-of-my-journey) |
